doc.field: Cabrillo National Monument is located on Point Loma, a high bluff at the entrance to San Diego harbor in California. Named after Juan Rodriguez Cabrillo, who, in 1542, was the first European to explore the west coast of the United States. Highlights of the park are Old Point Loma Lighthouse, the rugged shoreline, and the sweeping views across San Diego harbor.
